The paper discusses the challenges faced by digital forensic laboratories in law enforcement, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The proposed workflow management automation framework involves the use of servers and software, which falls under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the use of automation to simplify the preparation steps for digital investigators, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses the reduction of infrastructure costs and license fees, which falls under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
